      "content": "i mean i get that's the \"official\" explanation but i've seen the actual packet headers. they aren't just going to a microsoft server, they're being routed through a decentralized mesh that looks way more like a distributed computing network. if you look at the way the kernel logs capture micro-fluctuations in user input latency, it's too precise to be just \"performance telemetry.\" it's basically capturing the human reaction time at a subconscious level. dont you think it's suspicious that these \"privacy updates\" always seem to increase the frequency of these specific types of sensor captures?",
